.TH PHASORSTD_META 3 "April 2026" "Phasor 3.3.0" "Phasor Standard Library 3.3.0"
.SH NAME
phasorstd_meta \- Phasor VM introspection and meta-programming functions
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
.B using("stdmeta");
.PP
.B phs_version()
.B phs_op(opcode[, a, b, c])
.B phs_stack_run(opcode, ...)
.fi
.PP
.B Note:
.B phs_op()
and
.B phs_stack_run()
are only available in non-sandboxed builds.
.SH FUNCTIONS
.TP
.BR phs_version ()
Return the current Phasor runtime version string.
.RS
.PP
.B Arguments:
None
.PP
.B Returns:
String containing the Phasor version (e.g.\& \fB"3.3.0"\fR)
.RE
.PP
.TP
.BR phs_op (opcode, a, b, c)
Execute a VM opcode directly with three optional operands as per the ISA spec.
.RS
.PP
.B Arguments:
.RS
.IP \fBopcode\fR 12
Integer OpCode to execute
.IP \fBa\fR 12
First integer operand (optional, default 0)
.IP \fBb\fR 12
Second integer operand (optional, default 0)
.IP \fBc\fR 12
Third integer operand (optional, default 0)
.RE
.PP
.B Returns:
Integer result of the operation, or 0 if the operation does not produce an integer value
.PP
.B Throws:
Runtime error if
.B opcode
is not an integer, or if more than 4 arguments are provided
.RE
.PP
.TP
.BR phs_stack_run (opcode, ...)
Push arguments onto the VM stack, execute a VM opcode, then pop and return the result.
Operands are pushed in reverse order so they appear in the expected order when the opcode
executes. Only available in non-sandboxed builds.
.RS
.PP
.B Arguments:
.RS
.IP \fBopcode\fR 12
Integer OpCode to execute
.IP \fB...\fR 12
Operands to push onto the stack before execution (variadic)
.RE
.PP
.B Returns:
The value on top of the VM stack after execution
.PP
.B Throws:
Runtime error if
.B opcode
is not an integer
.RE
.SH EXAMPLES
.B Getting the Runtime Version
.PP
.nf
.RS
using("stdmeta");

var ver = phs_version();
.RE
.fi
.PP
.B Executing an Opcode
.PP
.nf
.RS
// Execute opcode 42 with operands
var result = phs_op(42, 1, 0, 0);
.RE
.fi
.PP
.B Stack Opcode Execution
.PP
.nf
.RS
// Push operands and execute opcode
var result = phs_stack_run(OP_ADD, 10, 20);
.RE
.fi
.PP
.B Version-Gated Behaviour
.PP
.nf
.RS
using("stdmeta");

var ver = phs_version();
if (ver == "3.3.0") {
    // Use features specific to this version
}
.RE
.fi
.SH NOTES
.IP \(bu 2
.B phs_op()
and
.B phs_stack_run()
are unavailable in sandboxed builds; attempting to call them will result in an
undefined function error
.IP \(bu 2
Operands passed to
.B phs_op()
that are not integers are silently treated as 0
.IP \(bu 2
.B phs_stack_run()
pushes arguments in reverse order to preserve natural argument ordering for the opcode
.IP \(bu 2
Direct opcode execution bypasses all safety checks enforced by the compiler; incorrect
use can corrupt VM state
.IP \(bu 2
.B phs_version()
reflects the version of the running runtime, which may differ from the version used to
compile the script
